'''拉斐尔·加马列尔·沃诺克'''（{{lang-en|Raphael Gamaliel Warnock}}，{{bd|1969年|7月23日||}}），[[美國|美國]][[美國民主黨|民主黨]]籍[[政治人物|政治人物]]、[[牧师|牧师]]和[[民權運動|民權運動]]的推行者，現任[[喬治亞州|喬治亞州]][[美国参议院|聯邦参议员]]。作为[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]的成员，他在2021年1月5日于[[喬治亞州|喬治亞州]]举行的美国参议院第2轮特殊选举中，击败了共和党原参议员凯利·洛夫勒（Kelly Loeffler）并获得了后者所保持的席位。<ref name="when-sworn-in">{{Cite news|last=Peebles|first=Will|title=Georgia runoff Senate races: When will we know the winners? Could there be a second runoff?|url=https://www.savannahnow.com/story/news/2021/01/04/georgia-senate-runoff-questions-answered-kelly-loeffler-raphael-warnock-jon-ossoff-david-perdue/4136131001/|date=January 4, 2021|access-date=January 6, 2021|work=Savannah Morning News|language=en-US|archive-date=January 6, 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141514/https://www.savannahnow.com/story/news/2021/01/04/georgia-senate-runoff-questions-answered-kelly-loeffler-raphael-warnock-jon-ossoff-david-perdue/4136131001/|author=|publisher=|accessdate=|format=}}</ref>

沃诺克成为了佐治亚州首位[[非裔美国人|非裔]]参议员，首位来自[[美國南部|美國南部]]的非裔民主党参议员，他与[[乔恩·奥索夫|乔恩·奥索夫]]也是佐治亚州自2005年来的首两位民主党参议员。自2005年以来，他一直担任[[亚特兰大|亚特兰大]]埃比尼泽[[浸信会|浸信会]]的高级牧师。沃诺克在《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|患者保护与平价医疗法案]]》扩大[[聯邦醫療補助|医疗补助]]的运动中担任领袖，以此在佐治亚州政治中获得了影响力。

== 早年生活和教育 ==
沃诺克来自于[[佐治亚州|佐治亚州]]的[[萨凡纳|萨凡纳]]。他在[[公共住房|公共住房]]中长大，是[[五旬節運動|五旬节派]]牧师韦琳（Verlene）和乔纳森·沃诺克（Jonathan Warnock）的十二个孩子中的第十一个。<ref>{{Cite web|title=From Public Housing to the People's Pastor: Savannah native uses pulpit as platform for change|url=https://www.wsav.com/news/from-public-housing-to-the-peoples-pastor-savannah-native-uses-pulpit-as-platform-for-change/|accessdate=2020-01-31|author=Lewis|date=2016-02-15|first=Ricardo|publisher=Wsav.com|archive-date=2020-01-31|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200131053316/https://www.wsav.com/news/from-public-housing-to-the-peoples-pastor-savannah-native-uses-pulpit-as-platform-for-change/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他的父亲在[[二战|二战]]期间曾在[[美国陆军|美国陆军]]服役，在服役期间他学会了汽车维修和焊接，随后他开了一家小汽修店，将废旧汽车修复后转售。<ref name="Reach">{{Cite book|first=Ben|last=Jealous|first2=Trabian|last2=Shorters|title=Reach: 40 Black Men Speak on Living, Leading, and Succeeding|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iU5rBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA227|date=2015-02-03|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=978-1-4767-9983-4|pages=227–|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2020-12-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201225070036/https://books.google.com/books?id=iU5rBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA227|dead-url=no}}</ref>

沃诺克毕业于索尔·约翰逊高中<ref name="savannah">{{Cite web|title=From Kayton Homes to King's pulpit|url=https://www.savannahnow.com/article/20061006/news/310069843|accessdate=2020-01-31|author=Clark Felty|date=2006-10-06|first=Dana|work=Savannah Morning News|archive-date=2020-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113092029/https://www.savannahnow.com/article/20061006/news/310069843|dead-url=no}}</ref>，由于他想追随[[马丁·路德·金|马丁·路德·金]]的脚步，他进入了[[莫爾豪斯學院|莫爾豪斯學院]]，获得了[[心理学|心理学]][[学士学位|学士学位]]。<ref name="wedding">{{Cite web|title=Ebenezer's Pastor Raphael Warnock to wed in public ceremony on Sunday|url=https://www.ajc.com/lifestyles/ebenezer-pastor-raphael-warnock-wed-public-ceremony-sunday/hwE4uGozpT3VhJlBhhxPgM/|accessdate=2020-01-24|author=Poole|date=2016-02-16|first=Shelia|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|archive-date=2020-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114052006/https://www.ajc.com/lifestyles/ebenezer-pastor-raphael-warnock-wed-public-ceremony-sunday/hwE4uGozpT3VhJlBhhxPgM/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="aa">{{Cite web|title=The Reverend Raphael Gamaliel Warnock, Ph. D.|url=https://www.aaheritagehouse.org/reverend-raphael-gamaliel-warnock|accessdate=2020-11-07|publisher=African American Heritage House|archive-date=2020-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113130810/https://www.aaheritagehouse.org/reverend-raphael-gamaliel-warnock|dead-url=yes}}</ref>沃诺克曾参加向上走（Upward Bound）项目，使认为该项目为帮助他上大学做好了准备，因为他可以通过萨凡纳州立大学提前注册大学课程。随后，他在[[哥伦比亚大学|哥伦比亚大学]]附属的[[纽约协和神学院|协和神学院]]获得了[[神學碩士|神學碩士]]、[[研究碩士|研究碩士]]和[[哲學博士|哲學博士]]。<ref name="Reach"/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Pastor at historic MLK Jr. church to speak at SU|url=https://www.syracuse.com/syracuse-university/2019/12/pastor-at-historic-martin-luther-king-jr-church-to-speak-at-syracuse-university.html|author=McMahon|date=2019-12-18|first=Julie|work=[[The_Post-Standard|The Post-Standard]]|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919093411/https://www.syracuse.com/syracuse-university/2019/12/pastor-at-historic-martin-luther-king-jr-church-to-speak-at-syracuse-university.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Who Is Raphael Warnock?: Everything To Know About Ebenezer Baptist Pastor Running For Georgia Senate|url=https://newsone.com/3900825/raphael-warnock-everything-to-know-georgia-senate/|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=Woods|date=2020-01-30|first=A.|publisher=News One|archive-date=2020-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200819230458/https://newsone.com/3900825/raphael-warnock-everything-to-know-georgia-senate/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 传教生涯 ==
在1990年代，沃诺克曾担任青年牧师，随后在纽约的阿比西尼亚浸信会教堂担任助理牧师。<ref name="pulpit_to_senate_2020_11_01_nytimes_com">{{Cite news|author=Fausset|first=Richard|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|title=Can Raphael Warnock Go From the Pulpit to the Senate?|date=2020-11-01|work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|accessdate=2020-11-20|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141540/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="republicans_paint_2020_11_19_politico">{{Cite news|author=King|first=Maya|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/11/19/raphael-warnock-georgia-republicans-438027|title=Republicans paint Raphael Warnock as a religious radical|date=2020-11-19|work=[[Politico|Politico]]|accessdate=2020-11-20|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141546/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/11/19/raphael-warnock-georgia-republicans-438027|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2002年，在[[马里兰州|马里兰州]][[巴尔的摩市|巴尔的摩市]]道格拉斯纪念社区教会担任主任牧师时，沃诺克和一名助理牧师被逮捕，并被指控妨碍警方对[[马里兰州|马里兰州]][[卡洛爾縣_(馬里蘭州)|卡洛爾縣]]一个教会经营的营地涉嫌虐待儿童的调查。沃诺克说，所谓的虐待不是性虐待，并否认试图阻止州警采访辅导员的任何错误行为。他说，他只是主张在面谈时律师应该在场。<ref name="Accused of obstructing probe">{{Cite web|title=City ministers accused of obstructing abuse probe|url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/bs-xpm-2002-08-03-0208030184-story,amp.html|accessdate=2020-11-10|author=Walker|date=2002-08-03|first=Childs|work=[[The_Baltimore_Sun|The Baltimore Sun]]|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141522/https://www.baltimoresun.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>沃诺克说，他进行了干预，以确保在一名青少年嫌疑人接受询问时有一名成年人在场。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ministers impeded probe, police allege|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/248367605/?terms=raphael%20warnock&match=1|accessdate=2020-12-11|date=2002-08-04|work=The News Journal|agency=Associated Press|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141554/https://www.newspapers.com/image/248367605/?terms=raphael+warnock&match=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>检察官撤销了对沃诺克的指控，州副检察官也承认这是一次 “沟通不畅”，并补充说，沃诺克协助了调查，起诉他是对资源的浪费。<ref>{{Cite news|title=2 ministers no longer facing charges of hindering probe|url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/news/bs-xpm-2002-11-07-0211070352-story.html|accessdate=2021-01-02|work=baltimoresun.com|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141532/https://www.baltimoresun.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Kertscher|first=Tom|title=PolitiFact - No proof Warnock 'ran over' wife; obstruction case dropped|url=https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2020/nov/16/erick-erickson/no-proof-warnock-ran-over-wife-obstruction-case-dr/|accessdate=2021-01-02|work=Politifact|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141548/https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2020/nov/16/erick-erickson/no-proof-warnock-ran-over-wife-obstruction-case-dr/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2005年，沃诺克成为[[乔治亚州|乔治亚州]][[亚特兰大市|亚特兰大市]]埃比尼泽浸信会的高级牧师，埃比尼泽浸信会是[[马丁·路德·金|马丁·路德·金]]的前会众，他是埃比尼泽浸信会成立以来第五位也是最年轻的高级牧师。<ref name="savannah"/><ref name="nyt-fausset-warnock">{{Cite news|author=Fausset|first=Richard|title=Citing 'Soul of Our Democracy,' Pastor of Dr. King's Church Enters Senate Race|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/30/us/raphael-warnock-ebenezer-baptist-georgia-senate.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=2020-01-31|date=2020-01-30|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141530/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/01/30/us/raphael-warnock-ebenezer-baptist-georgia-senate.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=McMahon|first=Julie|title=Pastor at historic MLK Jr. church to speak at Syracuse University|url=https://www.syracuse.com/syracuse-university/2019/12/pastor-at-historic-martin-luther-king-jr-church-to-speak-at-syracuse-university.html|accessdate=2020-11-21|work=Syracuse Post Standard|date=2019-12-18|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919093411/https://www.syracuse.com/syracuse-university/2019/12/pastor-at-historic-martin-luther-king-jr-church-to-speak-at-syracuse-university.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

作为牧师，沃诺克主张对[[特洛伊·戴維思|特洛伊·戴维斯]]宽大处理，他于2011年被处决。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Noted Reverend on Troy Davis: 'Moral Disaster'|url=https://www.theroot.com/noted-reverend-on-troy-davis-moral-disaster-1790865952|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=Dreyfuss|date=2011-09-21|first=Joel|publisher=Theroot.com|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141453/https://www.theroot.com/noted-reverend-on-troy-davis-moral-disaster-1790865952|dead-url=no}}</ref>2013年，他在[[巴拉克·奥巴马|巴拉克·奥巴马]]的第二任就职典礼上的祈祷仪式上宣告了祝福。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Preachers pray for unity at National Cathedral inaugural service|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/on-faith/preachers-pray-for-unity-at-national-cathedral-inaugural-service/2013/01/22/c2ecb2ec-64e0-11e2-889b-f23c246aa446_story.html|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=Banks|date=2013-01-22|first=Adelle M.|work=The Washington Post|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141552/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/on-faith/preachers-pray-for-unity-at-national-cathedral-inaugural-service/2013/01/22/c2ecb2ec-64e0-11e2-889b-f23c246aa446_story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2019年3月，沃诺克在他的教堂举行了一次关于[[全球变暖|气候变化]]的跨宗教会议，由[[阿尔·戈尔|阿尔·戈尔]]和威廉·巴伯二世主持。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Rev. Raphael Warnock, Ebenezer Baptist Church to host interfaith meeting on climate with Al Gore, the Rev. William Barber II|url=https://www.theatlantavoice.com/articles/the-rev-raphael-warnock-ebenezer-baptist-church-to-host-interfaith-meeting-on-climate-with-al-gore-the-rev-william-barber-ii/|accessdate=2020-02-01|author=Atlanta|date=2019-03-13|first=The|publisher=The Atlanta Voice|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141558/https://www.theatlantavoice.com/articles/the-rev-raphael-warnock-ebenezer-baptist-church-to-host-interfaith-meeting-on-climate-with-al-gore-the-rev-william-barber-ii/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 政治生涯 ==
[[File:Secretary_Salazar_Tours_Dr._Martin_Luther_King_Historic_Site_-_May_27,_2009_(3932075041).jpg|缩略图]]和沃诺克在[[马丁·路德·金国家历史遗址|马丁·路德·金国家历史遗址]]]]
沃诺克在乔治亚州扩大[[聯邦醫療補助|醫療補助]]运动中脱颖而出。<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|title='My ideals are driven by my faith': Raphael Warnock on his Senate runoff race|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/nbcblk/my-ideals-are-driven-my-faith-raphael-warnock-his-senate-n1246879|accessdate=2020-11-10|author=Bunn|date=2020-11-07|first=Curtis|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141521/https://www.nbcnews.com/news/nbcblk/my-ideals-are-driven-my-faith-raphael-warnock-his-senate-n1246879|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2014年3月，沃诺克领导了[[佐治亚州议会大厦|佐治亚州州议会大厦]]的[[靜坐示威|静坐活动]]，敦促各州立法者扩大《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|患者保护与平价医疗法案]]》所规定的[[聯邦醫療補助|医疗补助]]。他和其他领导人在抗议期间被捕。<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Atlanta's 55 Most Powerful: 51. Raphael Warnock|url=https://www.atlantamagazine.com/news-culture-articles/51-raphael-warnock/|accessdate=2020-02-01|date=2015-10-01|publisher=Atlantamagazine.com|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141456/https://www.atlantamagazine.com/news-culture-articles/51-raphael-warnock/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Arrests follow protests at state Capitol|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/arrests-follow-protests-state-capitol/EOf7FofLcwS6OKQ9i0OQzO/|author=Davis|date=2014-03-18|first=Janel|work=[[The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution|The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141457/https://www.ajc.com/news/arrests-follow-protests-state-capitol/EOf7FofLcwS6OKQ9i0OQzO/|dead-url=no}}</ref>2015年，沃诺克曾考虑参加2016年美国参议院竞选，竞争[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]人[[強尼·艾薩克森|约翰尼·伊萨克森]]的席位。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Exclusive: Pastor of historic Ebenezer Baptist Church considers U.S. Senate run|url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/exclusive-pastor-historic-ebenezer-baptist-church-considers-senate-run/QWxTEK6UM7NaO2MojR9StL/|accessdate=2020-01-24|author=Bluestein|date=2015-08-06|first=Greg|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141457/https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/exclusive-pastor-historic-ebenezer-baptist-church-considers-senate-run/QWxTEK6UM7NaO2MojR9StL/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他最后选择放弃竞选。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2015/10/02/pastor-of-mlks-church-will-not-run-for-georgia-senate-seat|title=Pastor of MLK's church will not run for Georgia Senate seat|work=[[The_Atlanta_Journal-Constitution|The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]]|author=Bluestein|first=Greg|date=2015-10-02|accessdate=2015-10-03|archive-date=2017-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706150819/http://politics.blog.ajc.com/2015/10/02/pastor-of-mlks-church-will-not-run-for-georgia-senate-seat/|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=The Jolt: Raphael Warnock prepares to run for Senate against Kelly Loeffler|url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/the-jolt-raphael-warnock-name-surfaces-potential-challenger-kelly-loeffler/HUBZdlsm7KH6EzYK6LbBDK/|accessdate=2020-01-24|author=Galloway|date=2020-01-13|first=Jim|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141500/https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/the-jolt-raphael-warnock-name-surfaces-potential-challenger-kelly-loeffler/HUBZdlsm7KH6EzYK6LbBDK/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

从2017年6月到2020年1月，沃诺克主持了新乔治亚州项目，这是一个专注于[[登记选民|选民登记]]的无党派组织。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Board chair named at the New Georgia Project|url=https://valdostatoday.com/news-2/local/2017/06/board-chair-named-at-the-new-georgia-project/|accessdate=2020-09-30|date=2017-06-08|work=Valdosta Today|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141557/https://valdostatoday.com/news-2/local/2017/06/board-chair-named-at-the-new-georgia-project/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt-fausset-warnock"/>

沃诺克支持扩大《[[患者保护与平价医疗法案|平价医疗法案]]》，并呼吁通过《[[約翰·路易斯_(喬治亞州政治人物)|约翰·刘易斯]][[選舉法案_(1965年)|选举法案]]》。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Fausset|first=Richard|date=2020-11-01|title=Can Raphael Warnock Go From the Pulpit to the Senate?|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|accessdate=2020-11-10|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141540/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":1"/>他还支持增加[[2019冠狀病毒病美國疫情|COVID-19]]救济资金。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/12/23/democrats-use-trump-2000-stimulus-checks-georgia-senate-race.html |title=存档副本 |access-date=2021-01-06 |archive-date=2021-01-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141559/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/12/23/democrats-use-trump-2000-stimulus-checks-georgia-senate-race.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>他是流产权利和[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]的支持者，得到了[[美国计划生育联合会|美国计划生育联合会]]的认可。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Fausset|first=Richard|date=2020-11-01|title=Can Raphael Warnock Go From the Pulpit to the Senate?|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|accessdate=2020-12-11|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141540/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/11/01/us/politics/raphael-warnock-ga.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite news|author=Bluestein|first=Greg|title=Georgia Senate: Abortion rights group backs Warnock's bid to unseat Loeffler|url=https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/georgia-senate-abortion-rights-group-backs-warnock-bid-unseat-loeffler/zWvgFfHEP4n0fd7j9EnZMO/|date=2020-05-20|work=The Atlanta Journal Constitution|accessdate=2020-12-11|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141502/https://www.ajc.com/blog/politics/georgia-senate-abortion-rights-group-backs-warnock-bid-unseat-loeffler/zWvgFfHEP4n0fd7j9EnZMO/|dead-url=no}}</ref>他反对隐藏携带枪支，并表示宗教领袖不希望在礼拜场所使用枪支。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gun Control Advocates Decry Revamped House Gun Bill|url=https://www.wabe.org/gun-control-advocates-decry-revamped-house-gun-bill/|accessdate=2020-12-11|author=Eloy|date=2014-03-12|first=Michell|work=WABE|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141532/https://www.wabe.org/gun-control-advocates-decry-revamped-house-gun-bill/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他长期以来一直反对死刑，他曾为死囚犯[[特洛伊·戴維思|特洛伊·戴维斯]]抱不平，尽管有证据证明他无罪，但他因杀死一名警官在2011年被处决。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Suggs|first=Ernie|date=2020-10-07|title=Profile of Raphel Warnock, candidate for George U.S. Senate|work=Atlanta Journal-Constitution|url=https://www.ajc.com/politics/warnock-election-profile/I3BUA24NKFHXVIUU3R3NG3WV2U/|accessdate=2020-12-15|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141510/https://www.ajc.com/politics/warnock-election-profile/I3BUA24NKFHXVIUU3R3NG3WV2U/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|author=Bigg|first=Matthew|date=2011-09-20|title=Clemency denied for Georgia death row inmate|work=Reuters News Service|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-execution-georgia/clemency-denied-for-georgia-death-row-inmate-idUSTRE78J2NP20110920|accessdate=2020-12-15|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141532/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-usa-execution-georgia/clemency-denied-for-georgia-death-row-inmate-idUSTRE78J2NP20110920|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 2020-21年美国参议院特别选举 ===
2020年1月，沃诺克决定参加佐治亚州美国参议院2020年特别选举，该位置当时由凯莉·洛夫勒（Kelly Loeffler）把持。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Raphael Warnock, pastor of famed church, enters Georgia Senate race|url=https://www.ajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/raphael-warnock-pastor-famed-church-enters-georgia-senate-race/sDPRVuKbd2w1QPZtrQrjMK/|accessdate=2020-01-31|author=Bluestein|date=2020-01-30|first=Greg|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141602/https://www.ajc.com/news/state--regional-govt--politics/raphael-warnock-pastor-famed-church-enters-georgia-senate-race/sDPRVuKbd2w1QPZtrQrjMK/|dead-url=no}}</ref>公开支持沃诺克选举的人包括民主党参议员[[查克·舒默|查克·舒默]]，[[柯瑞·布克|科里·布克]]，[[謝羅德·布朗|谢罗德·布朗]]，[[陸天娜|克尔斯滕·吉利布兰德]]，[[傑夫·默克利|杰夫·默克利]]，[[克里斯·墨菲|克里斯·墨菲]]，[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]，[[布萊恩·夏茲|布莱恩·沙茨]]和[[伊莉莎白·華倫|伊丽莎白·沃伦]]，民主党参议员竞选委员会，[[史黛西艾布拉姆斯|斯泰西·艾布拉姆斯]]以及前总统[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]和[[吉米·卡特|吉米·卡特]]。<ref>{{Cite news|author=Bluestein|first=Greg|work=The Atlanta Journal-Constitution|title=Jimmy Carter backs Warnock in crowded U.S. Senate race in Georgia|url=https://www.ajc.com/politics/politics-blog/jimmy-carter-backs-warnock-in-crowded-us-senate-race-in-georgia/64CJQ3T7GBFRJM7EJJYUV7S2UE/|date=2020-09-29|accessdate=2020-10-04|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141510/https://www.ajc.com/politics/politics-blog/jimmy-carter-backs-warnock-in-crowded-us-senate-race-in-georgia/64CJQ3T7GBFRJM7EJJYUV7S2UE/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="nyt-fausset-warnock"/><ref name="WarnockEndorsements1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/01/30/abrams-democrats-rally-georgia-senate-race-109561|title=Stacey Abrams, Dems rally around pastor in burgeoning Georgia Senate race|author=Arkin|first=James|date=2020-01-30|accessdate=2020-01-30|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141540/https://www.politico.com/news/2020/01/30/abrams-democrats-rally-georgia-senate-race-109561|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Elizabeth Warren|url=https://www.facebook.com/ElizabethWarren/photos/a.414227908686/10157656514423687/|date=2020-06-15|work=[[Facebook|Facebook]]|quote=As a champion for fair wages, Reverend Raphael Warnock has stood up for working families for years. I'm proud to endorse him because I know with him in the Senate, Georgians will have a leader with the courage and conviction to put working families first.|access-date=2021-01-06|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141512/https://www.facebook.com/ElizabethWarren/photos/a.414227908686/10157656514423687/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Obama endorses Warnock in crowded Georgia Senate race|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/obama-endorses-warnock-crowded-georgia-senate-race-73241066|accessdate=2020-09-25|author=Nadler|date=2020-09-25|first=Ben|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141515/https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/obama-endorses-warnock-crowded-georgia-senate-race-73241066|dead-url=no}}</ref>洛夫勒共同拥有的[[WNBA|WNBA]]球队[[亞特蘭大美夢|亞特蘭大美夢]]的几名球员穿上了为沃诺克代言的衬衫，以回应洛夫勒关于[[Black_Lives_Matter|黑人生命平权运动]]的争议性言论。<ref>{{Cite web|title=W.N.B.A. Players Escalate Protest of Anti-B.L.M. Team Owner|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/04/sports/basketball/wnba-dream-loeffler-warnock.html|accessdate=2020-08-20|author=Deb|date=2020-08-04|first=Sopan|work=The New York Times|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141534/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/04/sports/basketball/wnba-dream-loeffler-warnock.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在沃诺克竞选的最后争论集中在两千美金经济刺激救助金，他和[[乔恩·奥索夫|乔恩·奥索夫]]表示如果他们赢得了选举，民主党多数将在参议院批准该举措。<ref>{{Cite web|title=In Georgia, Democrats close with populist pitch vowing $2,000 stimulus checks|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/georgia-democrats-close-populist-pitch-vowing-2-000-stimulus-checks-n1252805|accessdate=2021-01-05|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210106141559/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/congress/georgia-democrats-close-populist-pitch-vowing-2-000-stimulus-checks-n1252805|dead-url=no}}</ref>

